The paper deals with the problem of federated learning over vertically partitioned data, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG). It also addresses the issue of entity resolution, which is a problem in databases (cs.DB) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper proposes a modified entity resolution algorithm that aims to avoid matching rows belonging to different classes, which involves making decisions based on noisy data, a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and cryptography (cs.CR). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.LG and cs.DB, followed by cs.AI, cs.CR, and cs.IR.
